<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Afrotropical (excluding Madagascar), Australian, Eastern Palaearctic, and Oriental regions (Fig. 321).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Polyphagous. This genus has been associated with herbaceous plants and shrubs belonging to many plant families (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Jolivet, P" journalOrPublisher="An essay about the relationships between the leaf-beetles and their food-plants. Backhuys Publishers, Leiden" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" title="Host-plants of Chrysomelidae of the World." year="1995">Jolivet and Hawkeswood 1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
About thirty species are known from Sub-Saharan Africa. Six species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Chevrolat, 1836" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1836" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hemipyxis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hemipyxis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hemipyxis</taxonomicName>
, known from Madagascar, are here transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Fairmaire, 1885" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1885" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Pseudadorium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudadorium" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pseudadorium</taxonomicName>
Fairmaire (see Notes in 
<taxonomicName authority="Fairmaire, 1885" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1885" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Pseudadorium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudadorium" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pseudadorium</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
